Police say a group of community members took to the streets in protest against the ongoing gang violence plaguing the area. CAPE TOWN A 33-year-old man and a 16-year-old boy have been shot dead in in Avian Park.The incident occurred earlier on Tuesday.Police say a group of community members took to the streets in protest against the ongoing gang violence plaguing the area.The police's Andre Traut said: Approximately 150 community members protested in the area regarding the violence. This group has since dispersed and the police will remain in the area to maintain law and order. The incident comes a day after provincial community safety MEC Dan Plato visited the area to encourage locals to bring about an end to the violence.